What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend it. It's a good gut class that fulfills a Science and QR credit and is not that difficult.

I would definitely recommend Movie Physics. The material seems more challenging than a normal GUT but the tests are not terribly difficult and Professor Robinson does his absolute best to ensure that everyone does well. I really appreciate that he made sure we understood what we were learning especially since non of us came into the class with much of a base in science.
Great class for QR/Science. TAKE IT!

Yes I would definately recommend this class to any other student, especially for someone looking for a QR. I have always struggled with math and this new way of learning it made a big difference to me.
Yes. This class was a great entry level course for physics.
I thought this was a well paced class, especially if you absolutely suck at math. Like, if 112 would be hard for you, take this joint.
I would definitely recommend this course to a student that isn't a science major because it can really help solidify his/her understanding of basic physics.
A great course, I would recommend it.

If you want to learn about physics in an approachable, non-traditional way, with an exciting teacher to make the entire process more enjoyable for you, then take this course. It deals a lot with estimation techniques and movie clips and helps with "general logical thought," whatever that means.
